President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for North Dakota, providing federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the area affected by severe storms and flooding from June 25 to July 1, 2014. The declaration allows for federal funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Lee K. dePalo has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.